The paper proposes a new type of prior for variational auto-encoders (VAEs) and extends it to a two-layer hierarchical model. The paper also provides empirical studies on six datasets and shows state-of-the-art results in unsupervised permutation invariant setting and comparable results to SOTA methods for the approach with convolutional networks. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a new method for training deep generative models. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the paper deals with image datasets and uses convolutional networks. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with neural networks and language models.
